e the magnetic field induces time oscillations that partially\nsuppress the lift-up effect, which is the primary transient growth mechanism\nfor the Navier-Stokes equations linearized around the Couette flow.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 Dec 2018 14:17:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-01"}
